text: Be careful on their Yu Tiao shop. They put straws into the oil to make the Yu Tiao more crispy.

It is just beside Kim San Leng Coffeeshop and also very near Bukit Panjang Market and Hawkercentre.There are quite a number of stalls selling Chinese, Malay and Western Foods.No coment on the foods as have not tasted them yet.The place has both inhouse sitting area and an extended covered outside sitting area.Both are not air conditioned, but had fans.For parking is at Multi Storey car park block behind.

Dated : 26/12/2018 ( Wednesday ).
Posted 11 photos.

Discovered Old Airport Wanton Noodle. Not sure its the real deal or just name sake. Turn out quite good. I'll give it a 8/10 for finer noodles, with  lard, wanton, size and taste, even soup is authentic wanton soup.
Love this neighbourhood coffee shop! Tanjong Rhu Wanton Noodle, best braised duck noodle, popular carrot cake, wonderful local pancake all at one place!
Best to avoid the western and Zi char stall if u want to live a healthy life. Msg-laced food
